---
title: Bistro Salmon and Lentils with Brussels Sprouts and Carrots
description: You’ll find saumon aux lentilles at many French-style bistros. But just because it has a fancy French name doesn’t mean that you have to be a fancy French chef to make it. Au contraire. It’s as simple as putting some veggies and fish in the oven to roast and boiling a pot of water to get those lentils cooking. On the plate, though, it’s still as impressive as anything a kitchen maestro could make.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/roasted-salmon-with-french-lenti-c67c0ece.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/roasted-salmon-with-french-lenti-1dcdce75.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/roasted-salmon-with-french-lenti-582c2a38cc7bd062103d26c2
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Fusion
nutrition:
  calories: 676 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 56 g
  fiber: 26 g
  sodium: 416 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Peel @carrots{1}(peeled and sliced on diagonal into ¼-inch pieces). Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce}(trimmed and halved lengthwise). Toss veggies on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} (leave room for salmon). Roast until lightly browned and softened, about ~{20%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Place @lentils{1/2%cup} in a #medium pot{} with @thyme{1/4%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, and enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook until tender, about ~{25%minutes}. Drain, discard thyme sprig, and set aside.

While veggies and lentils cook, halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}(minced). Halve @lemon{1}. Put @Dijon mustard{2%units}, shallot, and juice of half the lemon in a #large bowl{}. Whisk to combine and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Whisk in @olive oil{1%tbsp} and set aside.

With 10 minutes to go on veggies, add @salmon{12%ounce} to same baking sheet. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast until opaque and just cooked through, about another ~{10%minutes}.

Season cooked lentils with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Add to bowl with dressing and toss. Add carrots and Brussels sprouts and toss to combine.

Divide lentil salad between plates. Top with salmon and squeeze lemon juice (to taste) over everything.